Hellas Gold Greek Projects to Create 1,800 Jobs, Minister Says

-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l   a n d   A n t o n i s   G a l a n o p o u l o s
-- 
2011-10-21T12:29:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/hellas-gold-greek-projects-to-create-1-800-jobs-minister-says.html
Planned mining projects in Greece by
Hellas Gold SA, the Greek unit of  European Goldfields Ltd. (EGU) , will
create 1,800 jobs, Environment, Energy and Climate Change
Minister  George Papaconstantinou  said.  The projects, at mines in the Halkidiki region of northern
Greece, are worth a total investment of around 1 billion euros
($1.4 billion) and will generate annual revenue of around 125
million euros for the state, Papaconstantinou told lawmakers in
the Greek parliament in Athens today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
